<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1126" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1126">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/10–749: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                            the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-07">October 7,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received October 7—4:11 a. m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>4211. Message from <hi rend="italic">Flying Independent</hi> dated October 7
                        at 1115 hours local time stated vessel proceeding Fusan<note n="79" xml:id="d1126fn79">Pusan, Korea.</note> with official permission.
                        Departure was cordial. ETA Fusan October 9 at 0500 hours. No advice from <hi rend="italic">Flying Clipper</hi>.</p>
                    <p>Sent Department 4211, repeated OffEmb Canton 1149, Hong Kong 299, Taipei
                        342.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">McConaughy</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>